Dear Engineers,<br><br>At ATG, we strive to help people in their professional and personal lives. We are calling entries from engineers. Please read these rules carefully before submitting your entries.<br><br>1) Your post must be original, informative or educational and related to engineering.<br>2) We are looking for talented engineers who have worked on something exciting. Please share something that you have worked on, the challenges, experience or your learnings from the exciting task.<br>3) If point no. 2 does not apply to you, you better get started. We run a quarterly competition hunting the talent and nurturing, advising the curious. :) and remember even the best started from the bottom, so post right now even if you are not ready!<br>4) We are not looking for entries like : "what is xyz?", but are looking 
for : "How I started working on xyz and what did i learn from it" or "Why is XYZ a better approach then ABC?"<br>5) Top 10 entries will be rewarded. Top 3 entries will be awarded monetary compensation.<br>6) The number of upvotes on your post may help your post get noticed quickly, however, the winners will be decided solely by the jury.<br>7) The judges are :<br><br>Dr. Dibakar Rakshit, PhD, Assistant Professor at Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi<br>Nitish Garg, Founder - iQuest, Indian Institute of Technology, Mumbai<br>Prince Pahwa - University of California, Davis and Indian Institute of Technology, Roorkee<br><br><br><br><b>Last date for entries is : <u>20th May, 2017</u>.</b> Drop us an email at hello(at)atg.world with the title and the link. Winners will be announced on 10th June, 2017.<br><br>You are required to fill out your profiles completely along with the profile, cover pic and filling your bio here :&nbsp; atg.world/edit-user-bio<style>
